    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Octr 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revrd&#58; Is&#58; Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">From the friendly tone<lb/> of your letter to me when I applied to you for<lb/> a situation&#44; I have thought you might feel<lb/> satisfied to hear of my promotion since that<lb/> period&#44; and as patience &#38; perseverance is in all<lb/> situations of life necessary it has proved essential in<lb/> my case. I have sent you a transcript of an<lb/> article appearing in our papers&#44; which I know<lb/> you will find a space in your &#8220;Occident&#8221; for its<lb/> reception&#44; as all other articles relative to our people<lb/> I have been appointed assistant Hazan here in con<lb/>sequence of the physical inability of our Pastor<lb/> to perform all the duties&#44; but cannot be under any<lb/> other denomination during his life time&#44; my congre&#45;<lb/>gation seems to be very well satisfied&#44; which of course<lb/> from the style they have been accustomed to&#44; is no very<lb/> easy matter&#44; at any rate I have <del>&#63;</del><lb/> <del>&#63;</del> by his tuition approached him as near<lb/> as possible in style. I regret having heard that you had<lb/> withdrawn from the scene of your labors&#44; but I trust<lb/> ere long that you will resume those duties&#44; which<lb/> you have for so long so zealous by performed&#44; as a</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>faithful alborer in the vineyard of the Lord &#8220;but it<lb/> must be unsatisfactory to you to find from the<lb/> stubbornness of heart that all your persuasive elo&#45;<lb/>quence has been of little avail&#44; and that your uncea&#45;<lb/>sing labors&#44; have effected little good&#44; knowing the<lb/> forbearance necessary in your position&#44; but I trust<lb/> again that you will again enter the field&#44; and see<lb/> the successful result of your Labors</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">This being favored by a <persName>Mr Jacob<lb/> DaCosta</persName> one of our Congregants&#44; I have very little time<lb/> to spare but I shall continue to correspond should it<lb/> be congenial the following is an extract from the<lb/> &#8220;County Union&#8221; to which if you feel inclined you can&#39; make any Editorial Remarks.</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">Jewish Intelligence</p>
          <p>Our Jewish readers will feel some interest in learning<lb/> of the movements of our co&#45;religionists in the metropolis.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">the <persName>reverend Isaac Lopez</persName>&#44; a gentleman<lb/> who has held the appointment of Minister of the congre&#45;<lb/>gation of the Spanish &#38; Portuguese <del>Jews</del> Synagogue<lb/> upwards of 45 years&#44; has&#44; from indisposition natural<lb/> to advanced age&#44; he come incapacitated to perform<lb/> the whole of their duties belonging to his office&#44; which&#44;<lb/> during the period named&#44; have been faithfully performed<lb/> by him. The congregation have therefore acted wisely<lb/> in selecting an efficient assistant in the person of the<lb/> <persName role="author">Revrd Abm H. DeLevante</persName>&#44; who&#44; we learn <del>enl</del> from</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>the &#8220;Standard&#8221; entered upon his duties on <date>Saturday</date> last.<lb/> we join our contemporary in sincerely wishing the<lb/> Revrd. Gentleman every happiness in his new calling<lb/> enjoying as he does&#44; the confidence and good will of<lb/> the congregation&#8212;&#8221;County union</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In conclusion I beg to offer my<lb/> sincere regard to you hoping you may enjoy all<lb/> the happiness attending an earthly life and the<lb/> peace of a blissful abode in a hereafter</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">A DeLevante</persName></p>
			<p>address <persName role="author">Revrd A. DL</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Hebrew National Institution</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><addressee>Revrd Is&#58; Leeser</addressee></p>
